1 the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of $600,000, or so much of the sum as
2 may be necessary, to the secretary of state for the purpose of creating and distributing objective
3 and factual educational materials focusing on the accuracy, fairness, and readability of
4 measures placed on a statewide election ballot as provided in section 1 of this Act, for the
5 biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
6 SECTION 3. EXPIRATION DATE. This Act is effective through June 30, 2027, and after that
7 date is ineffective.
